1
00:00:08,958 --> 00:00:12,375
[NARRATOR] Long, long ago,
when the world was darker,

2
00:00:12,458 --> 00:00:15,041
the sky lit by fewer stars,

3
00:00:15,125 --> 00:00:17,458
the gods began to tire
of the dice game

4
00:00:17,541 --> 00:00:19,291
that would determine
who among them

5
00:00:19,375 --> 00:00:21,708
would hold dominion
over the world.

6
00:00:21,791 --> 00:00:24,166
And so, they created
many worlds,

7
00:00:24,250 --> 00:00:26,125
and beings to populate them:

8
00:00:26,208 --> 00:00:29,416
humans and elves,
dwarves and lizardmen.

9
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,958
These new creatures
began adventuring.

10
00:00:32,041 --> 00:00:36,041
Sometimes they were rewarded.
Other times they ended up dead.

11
00:00:37,791 --> 00:00:39,541
[PRIESTESS]
Incredible.

12
00:00:39,625 --> 00:00:42,458
[PRIEST] My compliments.
Was that some form of magic?

13
00:00:42,541 --> 00:00:45,041
No, it's just that once
you've mastered a technique,

14
00:00:45,125 --> 00:00:47,666
It can seem as though
you've cast a spell.

15
00:00:47,750 --> 00:00:50,791
Yes, well, next time I'll show
you what a dwarf can do.

16
00:00:50,875 --> 00:00:53,833
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
One, two.

17
00:00:53,916 --> 00:00:55,333
[ARCHER]
Huh?

18
00:00:57,208 --> 00:00:59,916
What are you doing?
My arrow killed them.

19
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,791
[GOBLIN SLAYER] They're
highly sensitive to smells.

20
00:01:02,875 --> 00:01:07,000
Especially the scents of women,
children, and elves.

21
00:01:07,083 --> 00:01:11,000
Ugh! No way! You keep
that filth away from me.

22
00:01:11,083 --> 00:01:12,875
You get used to it.

23
00:01:12,958 --> 00:01:15,875
[whimpering]

24
00:01:15,958 --> 00:01:18,916
-[ARCHER screams]
-[GOBLIN SLAYER grunts]

25
00:02:50,875 --> 00:02:54,208
[sword clanging]

26
00:02:57,375 --> 00:02:59,916
[PRIEST]
Interesting designs.

27
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,125
I believe this might
have been a shrine once.

28
00:03:02,208 --> 00:03:04,500
It looks like some kind
of battle took place here

29
00:03:04,583 --> 00:03:06,125
during the Age of the Gods.

30
00:03:06,208 --> 00:03:09,041
This could have been used
as a fortress.

31
00:03:09,125 --> 00:03:12,750
Whatever the case,
it was built by humans.

32
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:14,500
[PRIEST]
And after it was abandoned,

33
00:03:14,583 --> 00:03:16,291
the goblins made it their home.

34
00:03:16,375 --> 00:03:18,000
What a terrible jest.

35
00:03:18,083 --> 00:03:20,375
Speaking of terrible.

36
00:03:20,458 --> 00:03:21,833
Eww!

37
00:03:21,916 --> 00:03:23,625
This is so disgusting!

38
00:03:23,708 --> 00:03:27,583
Um, it does wash off
with water, mostly.

39
00:03:27,666 --> 00:03:31,125
I'm not gonna forget
about this when we get back!

40
00:03:31,208 --> 00:03:32,750
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Understood.

41
00:03:35,208 --> 00:03:37,083
I'm used to living underground,

42
00:03:37,166 --> 00:03:39,916
but being down here
feels wrong somehow.

43
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,666
[ARCHER] I think
we're walking in a spiral.

44
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:45,041
[PRIESTESS] I wonder
what's in the center.

45
00:03:45,125 --> 00:03:46,916
[ARCHER]
Wait, stop.

46
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,666
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
What's wrong? An alarm?

47
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:51,125
I think so.

48
00:03:51,208 --> 00:03:53,875
I only spotted it
because the marks are new.

49
00:03:55,583 --> 00:03:57,083
Conniving monsters.

50
00:03:57,166 --> 00:03:59,458
These ruins could be
full of traps.

51
00:03:59,541 --> 00:04:02,541
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] That's strange.
-What's the matter?

52
00:04:02,625 --> 00:04:05,041
-There are no totems.
-Huh?

53
00:04:05,125 --> 00:04:08,916
Um, that means, there aren't
any goblin shamans here.

54
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,625
Great.
This'll be a lot easier

55
00:04:10,708 --> 00:04:12,458
without any spells
flying around.

56
00:04:12,541 --> 00:04:14,375
[PRIEST]
Apologies, but that's not so.

57
00:04:14,458 --> 00:04:17,250
The lack of shamans
is disconcerting to him.

58
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:18,916
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Correct.

59
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,875
Ordinary goblins shouldn't be
able to set traps like this.

60
00:04:21,958 --> 00:04:24,291
[SHAMAN] You think someone
could be leading them?

61
00:04:24,375 --> 00:04:25,791
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
We should assume so.

62
00:04:25,875 --> 00:04:28,166
I have heard many tales
of the large nests

63
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:31,458
you bravely destroyed
in the past, Sir Goblin Slayer.

64
00:04:31,541 --> 00:04:33,250
What are your
preferred methods?

65
00:04:33,333 --> 00:04:36,250
[GOBLIN SLAYER] Smoke them out,
then crush them one-by-one.

66
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:38,958
Set them on fire,
drown them in the river.

67
00:04:39,041 --> 00:04:42,625
There are many options,
but those won't work now.

68
00:04:42,708 --> 00:04:45,375
-Are there tracks?
-It's hard to tell in here.

69
00:04:45,458 --> 00:04:47,291
The rock floor is too smooth.

70
00:04:47,375 --> 00:04:48,625
[SHAMAN]
Let's see.

71
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:53,750
Their hideout is
down the left hallway.

72
00:04:53,833 --> 00:04:57,083
-[PRIESTESS] How can you tell?
-The subtle wear on the stone.

73
00:04:57,166 --> 00:04:59,666
It looks like they travel
from the left side to the right

74
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:01,083
and then back again,

75
00:05:01,166 --> 00:05:04,666
or they head from their hideout
to the entrance.

76
00:05:04,750 --> 00:05:07,750
[PRIEST] What do you suggest,
Sir Goblin Slayer?

77
00:05:07,833 --> 00:05:09,541
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
We go this way.

78
00:05:09,625 --> 00:05:10,916
[ARCHER]
Did you not hear him say

79
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,333
their hideout's
in the other direction?

80
00:05:12,416 --> 00:05:15,833
[GOBLIN SLAYER] Yes.
But then we'd be too late.

81
00:05:15,916 --> 00:05:17,916
[armor jangling]

82
00:05:20,875 --> 00:05:23,250
[gagging]

83
00:05:23,333 --> 00:05:25,000
What an awful stench.

84
00:05:25,083 --> 00:05:26,666
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Breathe through your nose.

85
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:28,083
You'll get used to it.

86
00:05:28,166 --> 00:05:30,500
[thudding]

87
00:05:30,583 --> 00:05:32,625
[flies buzzing]

88
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,583
[ARCHER]
What is this place?

89
00:05:36,666 --> 00:05:37,958
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
A goblin waste heap.

90
00:05:38,041 --> 00:05:39,750
[ARCHER]
You don't mean...?

91
00:05:43,291 --> 00:05:44,416
[gasps]

92
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:46,541
♪

93
00:05:49,958 --> 00:05:51,833
[vomits]

94
00:05:51,916 --> 00:05:55,250
-What in the name of the gods?
-Poor miserable soul.

95
00:05:55,333 --> 00:05:59,625
-Please, you have to...
-She's still alive!

96
00:05:59,708 --> 00:06:02,541
-Quick, a miracle!
-Right!

97
00:06:02,625 --> 00:06:06,208
[gasps] What?
What is it, Goblin Slayer?

98
00:06:06,291 --> 00:06:10,041
-You must kill.
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] I understand.

99
00:06:11,083 --> 00:06:13,875
♪

100
00:06:13,958 --> 00:06:16,500
Wait! Please stop!
We can still save her!

101
00:06:16,583 --> 00:06:21,166
-[ARCHER] Don't!
-You must kill this monster!

102
00:06:21,250 --> 00:06:23,041
[growls]

103
00:06:28,875 --> 00:06:30,416
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Three.

104
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:32,333
I don't know what
you all were expecting,

105
00:06:32,416 --> 00:06:35,041
but I only came here
to slay goblins.

106
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:41,250
Kill them all,
every last one of them.

107
00:06:42,708 --> 00:06:44,000
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I will.

108
00:06:48,458 --> 00:06:51,458
[PRIEST] O horns and claws
of our father, Iguanodon,

109
00:06:51,541 --> 00:06:54,541
thy four limbs become two legs
and walk upon this earth!

110
00:06:54,625 --> 00:06:56,791
[air whooshes]

111
00:06:56,875 --> 00:07:01,000
A miracle from my ancestors,
the dragontooth warrior.

112
00:07:01,083 --> 00:07:03,625
Send this with him.
It should explain everything.

113
00:07:03,708 --> 00:07:04,958
[PRIEST]
Hmm.

114
00:07:05,041 --> 00:07:07,125
[clomping]

115
00:07:07,208 --> 00:07:08,791
Make haste.

116
00:07:08,875 --> 00:07:11,208
My conjured messenger
should safely deliver her

117
00:07:11,291 --> 00:07:13,083
to the elves in the forest.

118
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:15,250
[sobbing]
What the hell is going on?

119
00:07:15,333 --> 00:07:18,250
Can you imagine
what she's been through?

120
00:07:19,708 --> 00:07:21,708
[sighs]
Hmm?

121
00:07:21,791 --> 00:07:23,791
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I found something.

122
00:07:23,875 --> 00:07:26,041
[PRIESTESS]
Is it another scroll?

123
00:07:26,125 --> 00:07:27,916
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
A map of the ruins.

124
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,583
It was in this rucksack.

125
00:07:29,666 --> 00:07:31,791
The elf must have been using it.

126
00:07:31,875 --> 00:07:34,333
There's large chamber
to the left.

127
00:07:34,416 --> 00:07:36,416
They're likely using it
as their main camp.

128
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:39,500
-So, you didn't believe me?
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] I did.

129
00:07:39,583 --> 00:07:42,375
But the more information
we have, the better.

130
00:07:44,208 --> 00:07:47,875
You take this, ranger.
Let's go.

131
00:07:47,958 --> 00:07:50,000
[PRIESTESS]
Hey! Give her a second.

132
00:07:50,083 --> 00:07:51,916
[ARCHER]
It's fine.

133
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,208
[sniffles]
We have to move quickly,

134
00:07:54,291 --> 00:07:55,833
and stop them.

135
00:07:55,916 --> 00:07:57,458
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
That's right.

136
00:07:57,541 --> 00:07:59,833
The goblins
must be put to death.

137
00:07:59,916 --> 00:08:01,291
[arrow whizzes, thuds]

138
00:08:05,916 --> 00:08:08,666
♪

139
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:23,000
[sighs]

140
00:08:26,458 --> 00:08:28,750
[GOBLIN SLAYER] How many spells
do we have left?

141
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:32,333
[PRIESTESS] I only used Heal,
so I can pray for two miracles.

142
00:08:32,416 --> 00:08:34,666
I have three remaining myself.

143
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:37,458
But a dragontooth warrior
requires catalysts.

144
00:08:37,541 --> 00:08:41,416
I will only be able to use that
particular miracle once more.

145
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:44,000
And this old dwarf
can cast about four or five.

146
00:08:44,083 --> 00:08:45,500
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Got it.

147
00:08:45,583 --> 00:08:47,750
Would you like some water?

148
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:49,541
Yes, thank you.

149
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,958
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Show some moderation.

150
00:08:53,041 --> 00:08:56,041
Only a sip, a full belly
will slow your movements.

151
00:08:56,125 --> 00:08:58,916
She needs something to drink.
Can't you be a little more--

152
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:02,125
There's no need to act tough.
If you're up to this, come.

153
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:05,125
If you're not, go back.
It's that simple.

154
00:09:05,208 --> 00:09:08,458
[ARCHER] Don't be ridiculous.
I'm a ranger.

155
00:09:08,541 --> 00:09:11,541
Who's going to scout and find
all the traps if I leave you?

156
00:09:12,708 --> 00:09:15,750
[GOBLIN SLAYER] We'd just have
to make do with the four of us.

157
00:09:15,833 --> 00:09:19,291
Ugh, you idiot!
There's no way I'm going back!

158
00:09:19,375 --> 00:09:21,125
Not after what they did
to that elf.

159
00:09:21,208 --> 00:09:24,625
My home isn't very far
from here, what if they had...?

160
00:09:24,708 --> 00:09:29,208
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I see. Then let's begin.

161
00:09:29,291 --> 00:09:31,708
[SHAMAN] Keep your wits
about you, long ears.

162
00:09:31,791 --> 00:09:34,833
Stealth is our greatest ally
against the beasts.

163
00:09:34,916 --> 00:09:36,958
Did you know that dwarves
consider goblins

164
00:09:37,041 --> 00:09:39,125
our mortal enemies as well?

165
00:09:39,208 --> 00:09:41,791
We'll make them pay
for what they did to her.

166
00:09:41,875 --> 00:09:44,291
I won't leave here
until they're all dead.

167
00:09:48,041 --> 00:09:50,875
I hate taking advice
from dwarves, but you're right.

168
00:09:50,958 --> 00:09:54,500
Sorry for that just now.
I'll refocus.

169
00:09:54,583 --> 00:09:56,000
[chuckles]

170
00:09:56,083 --> 00:09:58,875
It sounds like your head's
back on your shoulders.

171
00:10:05,666 --> 00:10:07,708
[gasps]

172
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:10,708
[wind blowing]

173
00:10:15,958 --> 00:10:18,000
[gasps]

174
00:10:18,083 --> 00:10:23,250
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] Well?
-It's just as it looks.

175
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:26,166
-There are many.
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] Not a problem.

176
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:29,000
[PRIEST] Sir Goblin Slayer,
do you have a plan?

177
00:10:29,083 --> 00:10:30,458
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I do.

178
00:10:32,625 --> 00:10:34,541
[moans]

179
00:10:34,625 --> 00:10:36,666
[yawns]

180
00:10:41,416 --> 00:10:43,791
[grunts]

181
00:10:43,875 --> 00:10:46,708
Drink deep
and sing loudly spirits.

182
00:10:46,791 --> 00:10:49,291
Shout, dance,
and sleep like the dead.

183
00:10:49,375 --> 00:10:52,416
Show me the dreams
of fire wine!

184
00:10:56,333 --> 00:10:59,333
[gasps, chokes]

185
00:11:00,625 --> 00:11:02,125
[jangling]

186
00:11:02,208 --> 00:11:04,458
[PRIESTESS] Hear me,
O merciful Earth Mother.

187
00:11:04,541 --> 00:11:06,750
Grant us the peace
to accept all things,

188
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:08,708
and bless us
with your solitude!

189
00:11:08,791 --> 00:11:10,750
[muttering]

190
00:11:10,833 --> 00:11:12,875
[choking]

191
00:11:12,958 --> 00:11:15,250
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Stupor and silence.

192
00:11:15,333 --> 00:11:18,625
By combining those two magics,
the goblins will fall asleep

193
00:11:18,708 --> 00:11:21,208
before any sort of alarm
can be raised.

194
00:11:21,291 --> 00:11:24,625
And then, the three of us
will slay them up close,

195
00:11:24,708 --> 00:11:27,208
one at a time.

196
00:11:31,208 --> 00:11:33,583
[ARCHER grunting]

197
00:11:38,375 --> 00:11:40,416
[grunting]

198
00:11:43,416 --> 00:11:44,416
[grunts]

199
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:50,208
[ARCHER shudders]

200
00:11:50,291 --> 00:11:52,250
Too slick.

201
00:12:01,750 --> 00:12:04,916
[ARCHER] I see.
He's using their weapons.

202
00:12:07,416 --> 00:12:09,458
[grunting]

203
00:12:16,750 --> 00:12:21,958
Has he really been doing this
by himself this entire time?

204
00:12:27,625 --> 00:12:28,625
[gasps]
Huh?

205
00:12:38,458 --> 00:12:40,500
♪

206
00:12:41,833 --> 00:12:44,083
-[rumbling]
-[all] Huh?

207
00:12:44,166 --> 00:12:46,208
-[thudding footsteps]
-[air whooshing]

208
00:12:48,333 --> 00:12:50,958
[grunting]

209
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,333
[gasps]

210
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:00,000
[ARCHER]
An ogre!

211
00:13:00,083 --> 00:13:03,583
I thought those dirty goblins
were awfully quiet.

212
00:13:03,666 --> 00:13:07,041
They don't even
make good foot soldiers.

213
00:13:07,125 --> 00:13:09,791
You people seem more prepared
than that elf from before.

214
00:13:09,875 --> 00:13:11,666
But you're wrong if you think

215
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:14,416
you can step foot
in my fortress and live.

216
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:17,000
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Oh. So, you're not a goblin?

217
00:13:17,083 --> 00:13:19,333
Are you being serious?
He's an ogre.

218
00:13:19,416 --> 00:13:21,541
-You've heard of them!
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] No.

219
00:13:21,625 --> 00:13:24,708
Bastard. You mock me.

220
00:13:24,791 --> 00:13:26,666
I, who have been
granted an army

221
00:13:26,750 --> 00:13:28,791
by one of the demon lord's
generals.

222
00:13:28,875 --> 00:13:30,208
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I know there are powerful

223
00:13:30,291 --> 00:13:32,125
monsters in the world.

224
00:13:32,208 --> 00:13:34,375
But I'm afraid
I've never heard of you.

225
00:13:34,458 --> 00:13:36,541
[roars]

226
00:13:37,583 --> 00:13:39,208
[gasping]

227
00:13:39,291 --> 00:13:44,583
Then I'll show you my power,
so that you may die knowing it.

228
00:13:44,666 --> 00:13:47,041
Carbunculus crescant!

229
00:13:49,833 --> 00:13:51,791
He's casting a fireball!

230
00:13:51,875 --> 00:13:54,083
-[ARCHER] Scatter!
-[SHAMAN] It's enormous!

231
00:13:54,166 --> 00:13:56,500
Where do you propose we go?

232
00:13:56,583 --> 00:13:58,875
[PRIESTESS] Hear me,
O merciful Earth Mother.

233
00:13:58,958 --> 00:14:01,416
Please protect us, the weak,
with your divine light

234
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:03,958
and the sacred power
of nature!

235
00:14:05,125 --> 00:14:07,916
-Iacta!
-Protection!

236
00:14:10,375 --> 00:14:13,625
[grunting]

237
00:14:17,250 --> 00:14:19,750
O, Earth Mother...

238
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:23,083
Please protect us, the weak,
with your divine light

239
00:14:23,166 --> 00:14:26,166
and the sacred power
of nature once more.

240
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:28,291
Protection!

241
00:14:29,750 --> 00:14:31,083
[growls]

242
00:14:32,916 --> 00:14:34,916
-[rumbling]
-[PRIESTESS whimpering]

243
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:39,750
[whimpering]

244
00:14:41,458 --> 00:14:43,666
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
You saved us.

245
00:14:43,750 --> 00:14:47,375
-We can handle him.
-Foolish little archer.

246
00:14:47,458 --> 00:14:50,958
You'll suffer far more than
the other elf ever dreamed of.

247
00:14:51,041 --> 00:14:54,083
[GOBLIN SLAYER] Create
a warrior. We need numbers.

248
00:14:54,166 --> 00:14:56,250
As you wish, Sir Goblin Slayer.

249
00:14:57,958 --> 00:15:00,875
O horns and claws
of our father, Iguanodon,

250
00:15:00,958 --> 00:15:04,583
thy four limbs become two legs
and walk upon this earth!

251
00:15:07,708 --> 00:15:10,000
O sickle wings
of the velociraptor.

252
00:15:12,458 --> 00:15:15,833
Slice, fly, and hunt!

253
00:15:15,916 --> 00:15:18,875
-I request backup!
-You got it!

254
00:15:18,958 --> 00:15:21,416
Time to work,
you crafty gnomes.

255
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:24,625
Mash grains of sand together
to form mighty rock!

256
00:15:24,708 --> 00:15:26,666
Measly little dwarf!

257
00:15:26,750 --> 00:15:29,541
[grunts, groans]

258
00:15:29,625 --> 00:15:31,666
You damn cave dwellers
are too slow.

259
00:15:31,750 --> 00:15:34,875
We have our own way of fighting.
Observe, long ears.

260
00:15:34,958 --> 00:15:37,125
Stone Blast!

261
00:15:37,208 --> 00:15:38,583
[growls]

262
00:15:38,666 --> 00:15:39,875
[grunts]

263
00:15:39,958 --> 00:15:41,541
[growls]

264
00:15:41,625 --> 00:15:45,208
Did you think you could beat me
by throwing a few pebbles?

265
00:15:45,291 --> 00:15:48,208
[grunts]
Now, Sir Goblin Slayer!

266
00:15:52,916 --> 00:15:55,166
[grunts]
Is that your best attack?

267
00:16:00,041 --> 00:16:03,291
-Orcbolg, no!
-I don't think he's moving!

268
00:16:03,375 --> 00:16:06,458
Do not mistake me
for a mere goblin.

269
00:16:06,541 --> 00:16:09,166
-[grunts]
-[sizzling]

270
00:16:09,250 --> 00:16:12,875
You shall each pay dearly
for this humiliation.

271
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:17,000
First, I shall break
each of your limbs,

272
00:16:17,083 --> 00:16:20,166
then I'll make sport
of the females in front of you.

273
00:16:20,250 --> 00:16:22,875
[PRIEST] You will not defeat us,
Ogre. I swear it!

274
00:16:24,125 --> 00:16:25,166
[growls]

275
00:16:25,250 --> 00:16:26,791
Please attend to him,
Priestess.

276
00:16:26,875 --> 00:16:29,958
Goblin Slayer!
Please, can you hear me?

277
00:16:30,041 --> 00:16:33,250
[growls] Out of the way,
overgrown lizard.

278
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:36,000
Sir Mage and Lady Ranger,
now's your chance.

279
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:37,541
Hurry up with another spell,
dwarf!

280
00:16:37,625 --> 00:16:39,083
I'm working on it!

281
00:16:40,375 --> 00:16:43,500
You insolent bug,
stop your incessant buzzing!

282
00:16:43,583 --> 00:16:45,791
[grunts, screams]

283
00:16:46,750 --> 00:16:48,166
[grunts]

284
00:16:48,250 --> 00:16:50,458
Have another Stone Blast!

285
00:16:52,833 --> 00:16:55,000
Your attacks are useless.

286
00:16:58,291 --> 00:17:00,000
[roars]

287
00:17:00,083 --> 00:17:01,708
Come on, speak to me!

288
00:17:01,791 --> 00:17:03,708
[GOBLIN SLAYER grunting]

289
00:17:03,791 --> 00:17:07,375
I can't see well.
What's happening?

290
00:17:07,458 --> 00:17:09,916
Everyone's still
fighting the ogre.

291
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,333
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Good.

292
00:17:11,416 --> 00:17:14,250
I need a healing potion
and a stamina potion.

293
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:16,166
-Of course!
-Thanks.

294
00:17:18,541 --> 00:17:20,583
[GOBLIN SLAYER grunting]

295
00:17:21,625 --> 00:17:24,375
-Take them.
-[thunderous boom]

296
00:17:26,916 --> 00:17:29,375
[groans]

297
00:17:29,458 --> 00:17:31,250
-[glass shatters]
-Huh?

298
00:17:31,333 --> 00:17:33,791
-[GOBLIN SLAYER gulping]
-[glass shatters]

299
00:17:33,875 --> 00:17:36,958
Let's do this.
Where's my bag?

300
00:17:37,041 --> 00:17:39,041
It's right here.
What do you need?

301
00:17:39,125 --> 00:17:42,916
-Thanks. Stay back.
-Be careful!

302
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,666
[GOBLIN SLAYER] I'll be reckless
if it means I win.

303
00:17:45,750 --> 00:17:48,625
But there are usually
other ways to ensure success.

304
00:17:50,125 --> 00:17:51,833
Watch out! You're injured!

305
00:17:51,916 --> 00:17:54,708
I have a plan. Stand aside.

306
00:17:54,791 --> 00:17:56,458
All right. Kill him!

307
00:17:56,541 --> 00:17:58,541
My faith is with you,
beard cutter.

308
00:17:58,625 --> 00:17:59,958
Take him down!

309
00:18:00,041 --> 00:18:02,666
We find ourselves in dire
need of your assistance.

310
00:18:02,750 --> 00:18:04,750
[OGRE] I looks as though
the human weakling

311
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:07,958
has used up the last
of her miracles.

312
00:18:08,041 --> 00:18:12,625
Carbunculus crescant.

313
00:18:12,708 --> 00:18:14,625
No wait!

314
00:18:16,458 --> 00:18:19,541
Fear not.
If she manages to survive this,

315
00:18:19,625 --> 00:18:22,166
I'll allow her to live
for a little while.

316
00:18:22,250 --> 00:18:25,791
She'll be my plaything,
and then my food.

317
00:18:25,875 --> 00:18:29,000
I need someone to spawn
more goblins for me now.

318
00:18:30,166 --> 00:18:32,250
[growling]

319
00:18:37,833 --> 00:18:40,375
-Iacta!
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] You're a fool.

320
00:18:40,458 --> 00:18:42,666
[rumbling]

321
00:18:45,583 --> 00:18:47,250
[grunts]

322
00:18:47,333 --> 00:18:49,125
Huh?

323
00:19:01,291 --> 00:19:03,708
[wind blowing]

324
00:19:03,791 --> 00:19:05,750
[groans]

325
00:19:05,833 --> 00:19:07,500
[vomits]

326
00:19:07,583 --> 00:19:09,625
♪

327
00:19:10,875 --> 00:19:13,916
But how? What did you do?

328
00:19:15,458 --> 00:19:17,375
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
This is a gate scroll.

329
00:19:17,458 --> 00:19:19,750
I linked it
to the bottom of the sea.

330
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:24,333
What just happened?
Was that just seawater?

331
00:19:24,416 --> 00:19:26,958
[PRIEST] The water at that depth
is under incredible pressure.

332
00:19:27,041 --> 00:19:29,833
It must have been unleashed
swiftly, like a blade.

333
00:19:29,916 --> 00:19:33,958
To think, he used
a transfer scroll as a weapon.

334
00:19:34,041 --> 00:19:37,125
Such magic allows you
to escape in an instant.

335
00:19:37,208 --> 00:19:39,958
It's often used
by adventurers in peril.

336
00:19:40,041 --> 00:19:44,500
But certainly not as a form
of attack like this.

337
00:19:44,583 --> 00:19:46,333
[WITCH]
The thing is, dear.

338
00:19:46,416 --> 00:19:52,083
Your friend asked a strange
favor of me once upon a time.

339
00:19:55,208 --> 00:19:57,166
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I was going to use that scroll

340
00:19:57,250 --> 00:19:58,833
to destroy a nest.

341
00:19:58,916 --> 00:20:00,458
-Oh, well.
-[OGRE groaning]

342
00:20:00,541 --> 00:20:04,708
Now, then,
what were you called again?

343
00:20:04,791 --> 00:20:06,625
Not that it matters.

344
00:20:06,708 --> 00:20:08,208
You're insane.

345
00:20:08,291 --> 00:20:11,125
You would use such power
against mere goblins?

346
00:20:11,208 --> 00:20:13,583
-[grunts]
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] Yes.

347
00:20:13,666 --> 00:20:18,583
Because goblins are
far more troublesome than you.

348
00:20:18,666 --> 00:20:22,208
[OGRE groaning]

349
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:25,875
[MALE ELF]
You have our gratitude.

350
00:20:25,958 --> 00:20:27,750
We received your letter
and the girl,

351
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:29,666
then came as soon
as were able.

352
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:32,833
How many more goblins
are left inside at this point?

353
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:37,791
Well, anyway,

354
00:20:37,875 --> 00:20:40,250
we're going to go scout
for any survivors now.

355
00:20:40,333 --> 00:20:43,583
Please try to rest in the back
on the way into town.

356
00:20:48,208 --> 00:20:51,291
-Priestess.
-What is it?

357
00:20:51,375 --> 00:20:55,333
Does Orcbolg always do
insane stunts like that?

358
00:20:55,416 --> 00:20:59,083
Yes. That's just
who he is, I think.

359
00:21:00,375 --> 00:21:01,958
Well, then...

360
00:21:02,041 --> 00:21:04,125
[PRIESTESS] But despite
how rash he can seem,

361
00:21:04,208 --> 00:21:07,666
he's always quite aware
of his actions.

362
00:21:07,750 --> 00:21:10,583
He also isn't obligated
to teach me anything,

363
00:21:10,666 --> 00:21:12,916
and yet every quest he does.

364
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,458
I see.

365
00:21:14,541 --> 00:21:17,000
[snoring]

366
00:21:17,083 --> 00:21:19,041
-We should sleep.
-[PRIESTESS] Yes.

367
00:21:23,625 --> 00:21:26,291
♪

368
00:21:28,916 --> 00:21:31,625
Yeah.
No, I still don't like him,

369
00:21:31,708 --> 00:21:33,666
even if he did save us
from that ogre.

370
00:21:35,250 --> 00:21:38,083
I thought adventures
were supposed to be fun.

371
00:21:38,166 --> 00:21:40,625
There's joy in experiencing
the unknown

372
00:21:40,708 --> 00:21:43,083
and discovering new wonders.

373
00:21:43,166 --> 00:21:46,083
We should feel happy
or accomplished,

374
00:21:46,166 --> 00:21:47,833
proud of what we've done.

375
00:21:47,916 --> 00:21:50,875
But that's not what I'm
feeling in the slightest.

376
00:21:52,375 --> 00:21:55,750
Someday, I'll take him
on an actual adventure.

377
00:23:30,958 --> 00:23:33,541
-[trudging footsteps]
-[cows mooing]

378
00:23:36,625 --> 00:23:38,666
[gasps]

379
00:23:39,708 --> 00:23:41,750
Welcome home.

